.TH KOTONOHA 1 "2026-07-11" "kotonoha 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kotonoha \- Wayland desktop lyrics overlay for MPRIS media players
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kotonoha
.RB [ \-\-port
.IR PORT ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Displays a translucent, click-through, always-on-top overlay of word-by-word
synchronized lyrics for the current track, read from any MPRIS player over
D-Bus. On wlr-layer-shell compositors (KDE Plasma, wlroots) it floats above
fullscreen; on GNOME/Mutter and other compositors without wlr-layer-shell it
falls back to a normal top-most window.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-port " PORT" ", " \-p " PORT"
Override the Cider probe WebSocket receiver port (default 28745).
.TP
.B \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project homepage: https://github.com/locez/kotonoha
.SH AUTHOR
